41 void Parser::E_pdfstrcmp() {
42  Token T = cur_tok;
43  std::string s1 = sE_arg();
44  std::string s2 = sE_arg();
45  int cp = strcmp(s1.c_str(), s2.c_str());
46  TokenList L = token_ns::string_to_list(cp == 0 ? "0" : (cp < 0 ? "-1" : "1"), false);
47  if (tracing_macros()) the_log << lg_start << T << s1 << "==" << s2 << lg_arrow << L << lg_end;
48  back_input(L);
49 }

51 // Parses svn info. returns false in case of bad syntax
52 auto Buffer::svn_id(std::string &name, std::string &date, std::string &version) -> bool {
53  reset_ptr();
54  date = "0000/00/00";
55  version = "-1";
56  name = "";
57  if (head() == 'I')
58  advance();
59  else
60  return false;
61  if (head() == 'd')
62  advance();
63  else
64  return false;
65  if (head() == ':')
66  advance();
67  else
68  return false;
69  if (head() == ' ')
70  advance();
71  else
72  return false;
73  set_ptr1_to_ptr();
74  while ((head() != 0) && head() != '.') advance();
75  at(ptr) = 0;
76  name = data() + ptr1;
77  advance();
78  while ((head() != 0) && head() != ' ') advance(); // ignore file name extension
79  advance();
80  set_ptr1_to_ptr();
81  if (head() == '-') return true;
82  while ((head() != 0) && head() != ' ') advance();
83  at(ptr) = 0;
84  version = data() + ptr1;
85  advance();
86  set_ptr1_to_ptr();
87  if (wptr < ptr + 10) return true;
88  if (at(ptr + 4) == '-') at(ptr + 4) = '/';
89  if (at(ptr + 7) == '-') at(ptr + 7) = '/';
90  if (at(ptr + 7) == '-') at(ptr + 7) = '/';
91  if (at(ptr + 10) == ' ')
92  at(ptr + 10) = 0;
93  else
94  return true;
95  date = data() + ptr1;
96  return true;
97 }

99 // In latex3, a space is ignored, so locally redefine the catcode
100 void Parser::L3_getid() {
101  get_token(); // should be a dollar sign, but hack!
102  auto spcat = eqtb_int_table[uchar(' ')].val;
103  eqtb_int_table[uchar(' ')].set_val(10);
104  TokenList l = read_until(cur_tok);
105  TokenList info = read_arg();
106  eqtb_int_table[uchar(' ')].set_val(spcat);
107  read_toks_edef(l);
108  Buffer &B = local_buffer;
109  B.reset();
110  B << l;
111  std::string name, date, version;
112  B.svn_id(name, date, version);
113  new_macro(name, hash_table.ExplFileName_token);
114  new_macro(date, hash_table.ExplFileDate_token);
115  new_macro(version, hash_table.ExplFileVersion_token);
116  new_macro(info, hash_table.ExplFileDescription_token);
117  L3_logid();
118 }

131 // Complicated conditionals have the form \ifxxx ... \fi\c_zero{trueC}{falseC}
132 // the body contains \prg_return_true and \prg_return_false
133 // these macros expands \fi, \or, \else until finding \c_zero, then
134 // execute trueC or falseC. Defined as
135 // \expandafter\use_i:nn\__int_to_roman:w in latex,
136 
137 void Parser::E_prg_return(int c) {
138  Token T = (c == 0 ? T_use1 : T_use2);
139  scan_int(T); // let's hope this will not fail
140  TokenList L1 = read_arg();
141  TokenList L2 = read_arg();
142  if (tracing_macros()) {
143  the_log << lg_start << T << "#1#2->#" << (c == 0 ? "1" : "2") << lg_end;
144  the_log << "#1<-" << L1 << lg_end;
145  the_log << "#2<-" << L2 << lg_end;
146  }
147  one_of_two(L1, L2, c == 0);
148 }

150 // Generate #1#2#3 etc
151 // s is true when n is given by specification, false when by value
152 auto Parser::l3_parms_from_ac(long n, Token t, bool s) -> TokenList {
153  if (n < 0) {
154  err_buf << bf_reset << "Negative number of arguments " << n << " for " << t;
155  signal_error(err_tok, "bad args");
156  n = 0;
157  }
158  if (n > 9) {
159  err_buf << bf_reset << "Too many arguments " << n << " for " << t;
160  if (s) err_buf << " (wrong argument specification)";
161  signal_error(err_tok, "bad args");
162  n = 0;
163  }
164  TokenList L;
165  for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
166  L.push_back(make_char_token('#', 6));
167  L.push_back(Token(other_t_offset, '1' + static_cast<uchar>(i)));
168  }
169  return L;
170 }

172 // reads a command name, say \foo:nn, stores it in token_to_split
173 // sets tok_base = foo, tok_sig=nn
174 // return true if bad
175 auto Parser::L3_split_next_name() -> bool {
176  if (l3_get_name(err_tok)) return true;
177  Buffer &B = local_buffer;
178  B.reset();
179  token_to_split = cur_tok;
180  B << hash_table[cur_tok.hash_loc()];
181  bool ok = B.split_at_colon(tok_base, tok_sig);
182  if (!ok) {
183  err_buf << bf_reset << "Missing colon in macro name " << cur_tok << " by " << err_tok;
184  signal_error(err_tok, "no colon in name");
185  return true;
186  }
187  return false;
188 }

190 // user function, no error if missing colon
191 void Parser::L3_user_split_next_name(bool base) {
192  Token T = cur_tok;
193  if (l3_get_name(T)) return;
194  Buffer &B = local_buffer;
195  B.reset();
196  B << hash_table[cur_tok.hash_loc()];
197  B.split_at_colon(tok_base, tok_sig);
198  std::string res = base ? tok_base : tok_sig;
199  if (tracing_macros()) the_log << lg_start << T << cur_tok << lg_arrow << res << lg_end;
200  B << res;
201  TokenList L = B.str_toks(nlt_cr); // is this needed?
202  back_input(L);
203 }

224 // creates the name of the variant. foo:N this gives foo_p:N or foo:NTF
225 void Buffer::l3_fabricate_cond(const std::string &base, const std::string &sig, subtypes w) {
226  reset();
227  push_back(base);
228  if (w == l3_p_code)
229  push_back("_p:");
230  else
231  push_back(':');
232  push_back(sig);
233  if (w == l3_T_code)
234  push_back('T');
235  else if (w == l3_F_code)
236  push_back('F');
237  else if (w == l3_TF_code)
238  push_back("TF");
239 }

241 auto l3_ns::conditional_aux(const std::string &p) -> subtypes {
242  if (p == "p") return l3_p_code;
243  if (p == "TF") return l3_TF_code;
244  if (p == "T") return l3_T_code;
245  if (p == "F") return l3_F_code;
246  if (p.empty()) return l3_bad_code;
247 
248  err_buf.reset();
249  err_buf << "Bad specification '" << p << "' for " << token_to_split << " by " << cmd_name;
250  the_parser.signal_error(the_parser.err_tok, "bad spec");
251  return l3_bad_code;
252 }

254 // read variant and body, loops over variants
255 void Parser::L3_new_conditional_aux(TokenList &arg_spec, subtypes s) {
256  std::string spec = sE_arg_nopar();
257  TokenList body = read_arg();
258  Splitter S(spec);
259  for (;;) {
260  if (S.at_end()) return;
261  std::string p = S.get_next();
262  subtypes c = l3_ns::conditional_aux(p);
263  if (c == l3_bad_code) continue;
264  L3_generate_form(c, arg_spec, body, s);
265  }
266 }

268 // Constructs \foo_p:xx, \foo:xxT or \foo:xxF \foo:xxTF, completes body with
269 // either \c_zero \c_true_bool c_false_bool
270 // or \c_zero \use:n \use_none:n TA
271 // or \czero {} TA
272 // or \czero TA TB
273 // here TA and TB are the arguments of the new function.
274 // in the case \foo:xxT, after 0, there are 2 commands that read one argument,
275 // namely TA and either use or discard it. \foo:xxT is simpler
276 
277 void Parser::L3_generate_form(subtypes c, TokenList parms, TokenList body, subtypes s) {
278  body.push_back(Tc_zero);
279  Buffer &B = local_buffer;
280  bool pt = (s == L3_setp_code || s == L3_newp_code);
281  bool set = (s == L3_set_code || s == L3_setp_code);
282  switch (c) {
283  case l3_p_code:
284  body.push_back(Tc_true_bool);
285  body.push_back(Tc_false_bool);
286  if (pt) { // predicate, requires non-protected
287  err_buf.reset();
288  err_buf << cmd_name << " for \\" << tok_base << ":" << tok_sig << ": A predicate cannot be protected";
289  signal_error(err_tok, "bad protected");
290  }
291  break;
292  case l3_T_code: // T
293  body.push_back(T_usen);
294  body.push_back(T_use_nonen);
295  break;
296  case l3_F_code: // F
297  body.push_back(hash_table.OB_token);
298  body.push_back(hash_table.CB_token);
299  break;
300  // case L3_TF_code: TF nothing to be done
301  default:;
302  }
303  B.l3_fabricate_cond(tok_base, tok_sig, c);
304  brace_me(body);
305  back_input(body);
306  back_input(parms);
307  back_input(hash_table.locate(B));
308  cur_tok = cmd_name;
309  M_def(false, false, pt ? userp_cmd : user_cmd, set ? rd_always : rd_if_undef);
310 }

312 // Case of
313 // \prg_new_eq_conditional:NNn \tl_if_exist:N \cs_if_exist:N { TF , T , F , p }
314 // rename X-extended into Y-extended
315 
316 void Parser::L3_eq_conditional(subtypes s) {
317  cmd_name = cur_tok;
318  how_to_generate = s;
319  if (L3_split_next_name()) {
320  read_arg();
321  read_arg();
322  return;
323  }
324  std::string tok_base1 = tok_base;
325  std::string tok_sig1 = tok_sig;
326  bool bad = L3_split_next_name();
327  std::string spec = sE_arg_nopar();
328  if (bad) return;
329  Buffer & B = local_buffer;
330  Splitter S(spec);
331  for (;;) {
332  if (S.at_end()) return;
333  std::string p = S.get_next();
334  subtypes c = l3_ns::conditional_aux(p);
335  if (c == l3_bad_code) continue;
336  B.l3_fabricate_cond(tok_base, tok_sig, c);
337  if (!hash_table.is_defined(B)) {
338  parse_error(err_tok, "Undefined token", B.c_str());
339  continue;
340  }
341  Token old = hash_table.last_tok;
342  B.l3_fabricate_cond(tok_base1, tok_sig1, c);
343  Token newt = hash_table.locate(B);
344  cur_tok = cmd_name;
345  M_let(newt, old, false, how_to_generate == L3_new_code);
346  }
347 }

349 // This implements the variants, assuming the truth value is in test
350 // \prg_new_conditional:Npnn fun args { p , T , F , TF }
351 // \if_some_test \prg_return_true: \else: \prg_return_false: \fi:
352 
353 void Parser::l3_after_cond(Token T, bool test, subtypes c) {
354  TokenList res;
355  switch (c) {
356  case l3_p_code:
357  if (test)
358  res.push_back(Tc_true_bool);
359  else
360  res.push_back(Tc_false_bool);
361  break;
362  case l3_TF_code: {
363  TokenList A = read_arg();
364  TokenList B = read_arg();
365  if (test)
366  res = A;
367  else
368  res = B;
369  break;
370  }
371  case l3_T_code: {
372  TokenList L = read_arg();
373  if (test) res = L;
374  break;
375  }
376  case l3_F_code: {
377  TokenList L = read_arg();
378  if (!test) res = L;
379  break;
380  }
381  default: return; // should not happen
382  }
383  if (tracing_macros()) the_log << lg_start << T << lg_arrow << res << lg_end;
384  back_input(res);
385 }

387 // Implements variants of \cs_if_eq:NN
388 void Parser::E_l3_ifx(subtypes c) {
389  Token caller = cur_tok;
390  Token a1, a2;
391  if (c >= 8) {
392  c = subtypes(c - 8);
393  csname_arg();
394  }
395  read_token_arg(caller);
396  a1 = cur_tok;
397  if (c >= 4) {
398  c = subtypes(c - 4);
399  csname_arg();
400  }
401  read_token_arg(caller);
402  a2 = cur_tok;
403  back_input(a1);
404  back_input(a2);
405  bool res = E_ifx();
406  return l3_after_cond(caller, res, c);
407 }

409 // In latex3, \str_if_eq:nn uses \unexpanded; this produces a character string
410 // converted to a token list, then back to character string. Simplified here.
411 // There is a variant \str_if_eq_x:nn with with full expansion
412 // and two variants v and o (for each argument).
413 
414 auto Parser::l3_to_string(subtypes c, TokenList &L) -> std::string {
415  switch (c) {
416  case l3expx_code: read_toks_edef(L); break;
417  case l3expo_code: l3_reexpand_o(L); break;
418  case l3expV_code: l3_expand_Vv(L, false); break;
419  default:;
420  }
421  group_buffer.reset();
422  group_buffer << L;
423  return group_buffer.to_string();
424 }

426 void Parser::E_l3str_ifeq(subtypes c) {
427  Token caller = cur_tok;
428  subtypes exp1 = l3expn_code;
429  subtypes exp2 = l3expn_code;
430  if (c >= 24) {
431  exp1 = l3expV_code;
432  exp2 = l3expV_code;
433  c = subtypes(c - 24);
434  } else if (c >= 20) {
435  exp2 = l3expV_code;
436  c = subtypes(c - 20);
437  } else if (c >= 16) {
438  exp2 = l3expo_code;
439  c = subtypes(c - 16);
440  } else if (c >= 12) {
441  exp1 = l3expo_code;
442  c = subtypes(c - 12);
443  } else if (c >= 8) {
444  exp1 = l3expV_code;
445  c = subtypes(c - 8);
446  } else if (c >= 4) {
447  exp1 = l3expx_code;
448  exp2 = l3expx_code;
449  c = subtypes(c - 4);
450  }
451 
452  TokenList a1 = read_arg();
453  TokenList a2 = read_arg();
454  std::string s1 = l3_to_string(exp1, a1);
455  std::string s2 = l3_to_string(exp2, a2);
456  l3_after_cond(caller, s1 == s2, c);
457 }

459 // Args: string to compare, case a-list, plus additional args
460 void Parser::E_l3str_case(subtypes c) {
461  subtypes exp = l3expn_code;
462  if (c >= 8) {
463  exp = l3expo_code;
464  c = subtypes(c - 8);
465  }
466  if (c >= 4) {
467  exp = l3expx_code;
468  c = subtypes(c - 4);
469  }
470  Token caller = cur_tok;
471  TokenList true_res, false_res, res;
472  TokenList as1 = read_arg();
473  TokenList clauses = read_arg();
474  if (c == l3_TF_code || c == l3_T_code) true_res = read_arg();
475  if (c == l3_TF_code || c == l3_F_code) false_res = read_arg();
476  bool match = false;
477  std::string s1 = l3_to_string(exp, as1);
478  if (exp == l3expo_code) exp = l3expn_code;
479  if (tracing_macros()) the_log << lg_start << caller << " compares " << s1 << lg_end;
480  for (;;) {
481  token_ns::remove_initial_spaces(clauses);
482  if (clauses.empty()) break;
483  TokenList as2 = token_ns::get_a_param(clauses, false);
484  // should we check for bad termination?
485  TokenList code = token_ns::get_a_param(clauses, false);
486  std::string s2 = l3_to_string(exp, as2);
487  if (s1 == s2) {
488  match = true;
489  res = code;
490  break;
491  }
492  }
493  if (match)
494  res.splice(res.end(), true_res);
495  else
496  res.splice(res.end(), false_res);
497  if (tracing_macros()) the_log << lg_start << caller << lg_arrow << res << lg_end;
498  back_input(res);
499 }

501 void Parser::L3_check_cmd(int c) {
502  Token T = cur_tok;
503  Token what;
504  if (c == 1 || c == 3) {
505  std::string name = sE_arg_nopar();
506  what = hash_table.locate(name);
507  } else {
508  if (l3_get_name(T)) return;
509  what = cur_tok;
510  }
511  bool is_free = hash_table.eqtb[what.eqtb_loc()].is_undef_or_relax();
512  if (c == 0 || c == 1) {
513  if (!is_free) bad_redefinition(0, what);
514  } else {
515  if (is_free) bad_redefinition(1, what);
516  }
517 }

522 // \tl_new:N and variants (14); half of them are \tl_new:c
523 void Parser::l3_new_token_list(int c) {
524  bool c_name = false;
525  if (c >= l3_tlx_new_code) {
526  c -= l3_tlx_new_code;
527  c_name = true;
528  }
529  Token name = fetch_csname(c_name);
530  if (c == l3_tl_clear_code || c == l3_tl_gclear_code) {
531  M_let(name, T_empty, c == l3_tl_gclear_code, false);
532  return;
533  }
534  bool u = hash_table.eqtb[name.eqtb_loc()].is_undef_or_relax();
535  if (c == l3_tl_gclearnew_code || c == l3_tl_clearnew_code) {
536  // define globally, reset locally
537  if (u)
538  M_let(name, T_empty, true, false);
539  else
540  M_let(name, T_empty, c == l3_tl_gclearnew_code, false);
541  return;
542  }
543  if (!u) bad_redefinition(0, name);
544  if (c == l3_tl_new_code) {
545  M_let(name, T_empty, true, false);
546  return;
547  }
548  TokenList L;
549  if (c == l3_tl_const_code) {
550  L = read_arg();
551  } else
552  l3_expand_x(L);
553  new_macro(L, name, true);
554 }

558 
559 // \tl_set:Nn and variants. Second argument is (by default) expanded once
560 // There are 24 variants; missing Npc
561 void Parser::l3_tl_set(int c) {
562  bool gbl = false;
563  bool c_arg = false;
564  if (c >= 18) {
565  gbl = true;
566  c -= 18;
567  }
568  if (c >= 9) {
569  c_arg = true;
570  c -= 9;
571  }
572  Token name = fetch_csname(c_arg);
573  // TODO: if(check_declaration) check name is not undef_or_relax
574  TokenList res;
575  switch (c) {
576  case l3expn_code: res = scan_general_text(); break;
577  case l3expo_code: l3_expand_o(res); break;
578  case l3expx_code: l3_expand_x(res); break;
579  case l3expv_code:
580  csname_arg();
581  l3_expand_Vv(res, true);
582  break;
583  case l3expV_code:
584  res = read_arg();
585  l3_expand_Vv(res, false);
586  break;
587  case l3expf_code: l3_expand_f(res); break;
588  default: parse_error(err_tok, "internal error unimplemented", err_tok, "", "internal error"); return;
589  }
590  new_macro(res, name, gbl);
591 }

608 // \tl_put_left:Nn and variants. Second argument is (by default) expanded once
609 // There are 16 variants: nVox
610 void Parser::l3_tl_put_left(int c) {
611  bool gbl = false;
612  bool c_arg = false;
613  bool put_left = true;
614  if (c >= 36) {
615  put_left = false;
616  c -= 36;
617  }
618  if (c >= 18) {
619  gbl = true;
620  c -= 18;
621  }
622  if (c >= 9) {
623  c_arg = true;
624  c -= 9;
625  }
626  Token name = fetch_csname(c_arg);
627  // TODO: if(check_declaration) check name not undef_or_relax
628  TokenList res;
629  switch (c) {
630  case l3expn_code: res = scan_general_text(); break;
631  case l3expo_code: l3_expand_o(res); break;
632  case l3expx_code: l3_expand_x(res); break;
633  case l3expV_code:
634  res = read_arg();
635  l3_expand_Vv(res, false);
636  break;
637  default: parse_error(err_tok, "internal error unimplemented ", err_tok, "", "internal error"); return;
638  }
639  TokenList cur = get_mac_value(name);
640  if (put_left)
641  cur.splice(cur.begin(), res);
642  else
643  cur.splice(cur.end(), res);
644  new_macro(cur, name, gbl);
645 }

647 // set rescan and variant 12 variants + 1
648 void Parser::tl_set_rescan(int c) {
649  bool special = false;
650  if (c == 12) {
651  special = true;
652  c = 0;
653  }
654  bool gbl = false;
655  if (c >= 6) {
656  gbl = true;
657  c -= 6;
658  }
659  bool cflag = false;
660  if (c >= 3) {
661  cflag = true;
662  c -= 3;
663  }
664  Token name;
665  if (!special) name = fetch_csname(cflag);
666  TokenList side_effects = read_arg();
667  TokenList arg;
668  if (c == 0)
669  arg = read_arg();
670  else if (c == 1)
671  l3_expand_o(arg);
672  else
673  l3_expand_x(arg);
674  TokenList res;
675  push_level(bt_brace);
676  word_define(endlinechar_code, -1, false);

728 // \char_set_catcode:nn{110}{`A+1} and variants: \the or \showthe
729 void Parser::L3_set_num_code(int c) {
730  int offset = 0;
731  int max = 0;
732  bool show = false;
733  switch (c) {
734  case setcat_code:
735  offset = 0;
736  max = 15;
737  break;
738  case thecat_code: offset = 0; break;
739  case showcat_code:
740  offset = 0;
741  show = true;
742  break;
743  case setmath_code:
744  offset = math_code_offset;
745  max = 0100000;
746  break;
747  case themath_code: offset = math_code_offset; break;
748  case showmath_code:
749  offset = math_code_offset;
750  show = true;
751  break;
752  case setlc_code:
753  offset = lc_code_offset;
754  max = nb_characters - 1;
755  break;
756  case thelc_code: offset = lc_code_offset; break;
757  case showlc_code:
758  offset = lc_code_offset;
759  show = true;
760  break;
761  case setuc_code:
762  offset = uc_code_offset;
763  max = nb_characters - 1;
764  break;
765  case theuc_code: offset = uc_code_offset; break;
766  case showuc_code:
767  offset = uc_code_offset;
768  show = true;
769  break;
770  case setsf_code:
771  offset = sf_code_offset;
772  max = 077777;
773  break;
774  case thesf_code: offset = sf_code_offset; break;
775  case showsf_code:
776  offset = sf_code_offset;
777  show = true;
778  break;
779  }
780  Token T = cur_tok;
781  if (max != 0) {
782  TokenList L1 = read_arg();

786  N = 0;
787  }

792  return;
793  }

805  B.reset();

807  TokenList res = B.str_toks(nlt_space);
808  back_input(res);
809  }
810 }

831 // \token_if_eq_catcode and variants
832 void Parser::l3_token_check(subtypes c) {
833  Token caller = cur_tok;
834  bool res = false;
835  switch (c / 4) {
836  case tok_eq_meaning_code: res = E_ifx(); break;
837  case tok_eq_cat_code: // \token_if_eq_catcode:NN
838  case tok_eq_char_code: // \token_if_eq_charcode:NN
839  {
840  symcodes a1;
841  subtypes b1;
842  symcodes a2;
843  subtypes b2;
844  if (!l3_get_cat(a1, b1, caller))
845  if (!l3_get_cat(a2, b2, caller)) res = ((c / 4) == tok_eq_cat_code ? a1 == a2 : b1 == b2);
846  break;
847  }
848  case tok_if_cs_code: {
849  symcodes a1;
850  subtypes b1;
851  if (!l3_get_cat(a1, b1, caller)) res = a1 == relax_cmd;
852  break;
853  }
854  case tok_if_macro_code:
855  if (read_token_arg(caller)) break;
856  res = (cur_cmd_chr.is_user());
857  break;
858  case tok_if_long_code:
859  if (read_token_arg(caller)) break;
860  res = (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == userl_cmd);
861  break;
862  case tok_if_prot_code:
863  if (read_token_arg(caller)) break;
864  res = (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == userp_cmd);
865  break;
866  case tok_if_longprot_code:
867  if (read_token_arg(caller)) break;
868  res = (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == userlp_cmd);
869  break;
870  case tok_if_expandable_code:
871  if (read_token_arg(caller)) break;
872  if (cur_cmd_chr.is_undef())
873  res = false;
874  else
875  res = (cur_cmd_chr.is_expandable());
876  break;
877  case tok_if_chardef_code:
878  if (read_token_arg(caller))
879  break;
880  else
881  res = (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == char_given_cmd);
882  break;
883  case tok_if_mathchardef_code:
884  if (read_token_arg(caller))
885  break;
886  else
887  res = (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == math_given_cmd);
888  break;
889  case tok_if_dim_code:
890  if (read_token_arg(caller))
891  break;
892  else
893  res = (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == assign_dimen_cmd && cur_cmd_chr.chr < int(nb_registers));
894  break;
895  case tok_if_skip_code:
896  if (read_token_arg(caller))
897  break;
898  else
899  res = (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == assign_glue_cmd && cur_cmd_chr.chr < int(nb_registers));
900  break;
901  case tok_if_muskip_code:
902  if (read_token_arg(caller))
903  break;
904  else
905  res = (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == assign_mu_glue_cmd && cur_cmd_chr.chr >= muskip_reg_offset);
906  break;
907  case tok_if_toks_code:
908  if (read_token_arg(caller))
909  break;
910  else
911  res = (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == assign_toks_cmd && int(cur_cmd_chr.chr) < int(nb_registers));
912  break;
913  case tok_if_int_code:
914  if (read_token_arg(caller))
915  break;
916  else
917  res = (cur_cmd_chr.cmd == assign_int_cmd && cur_cmd_chr.chr >= count_reg_offset &&
918  cur_cmd_chr.chr < int(count_reg_offset + nb_registers));
919  break;
920  case tok_if_primitive_code:
921  if (read_token_arg(caller)) break;
922  {
923  symcodes K = cur_cmd_chr.cmd;
924  if (K == undef_cmd)
925  res = false; // undefined
926  else if (K >= user_cmd)
927  res = false; // macro
928  else if (K < 16)
929  res = false; // character
930  else
931  res = true;
932  }
933  }
934 
935  l3_after_cond(caller, res, subtypes(c % 4));
936 }

1014 // \cs_generate_variant:Nn \foo:nnn {Vn, xV}
1015 // produces \def\foo:Vnn{\exp_args:NV \foo:nnn}
1016 // and \protected\def\foo:xVn{\exp_args:NV \foo:xVn}

1018 void Parser::l3_generate_variant() {
1019  bool nok = L3_split_next_name();
1020  Token orig = cur_tok;
1021  bool prot = false; // do we need to protect
1022  if (!cur_cmd_chr.is_expandable()) prot = true;
1023  if (cur_cmd_chr.cmd >= userp_cmd) prot = true;
1024  if (cur_cmd_chr.is_undef()) {
1025  undefined_mac();
1026  nok = true;
1027  }
1028  std::string spec = sE_arg_nopar();
1029  if (nok) return; // an error has already been generated
1030  if (tracing_commands()) the_log << lg_startbrace << "Generating variants for " << orig << " with " << spec << lg_endbrace;
1031  Splitter S(spec);
1032  for (;;) {
1033  if (S.at_end()) return;
1034  std::string p = S.get_next();
1035  l3_generate_variant(p, prot, orig);
1036  }
1037 }

1050 // This produces a single variant;
1051 void Parser::l3_generate_variant(const std::string &var, bool prot, Token orig) {
1052  auto n = var.size();
1053  if (n == 0) return; // ignore empty sepc
1054  if (n > tok_sig.size()) {
1055  err_buf.reset();
1056  err_buf << "New spec size '" << var << "' too big for " << orig;
1057  signal_error(err_tok, "spec too big");
1058  return;
1059  }
1060  Buffer &osig = local_buffer;
1061  Buffer &nsig = local_bufferB;
1062  Buffer &changes = local_bufferC;
1063  osig << bf_reset << tok_sig;
1064  nsig << bf_reset << var;
1065  changes.reset();
1066  size_t last_ok = 0;
1067  for (size_t i = 0; i < n; i++) {
1068  char oc = osig[i], nc = nsig[i];
1069  if (oc == nc) { // no conversion needed
1070  if (!(nc == 'N' || nc == 'p')) nc = 'n'; // cannot always use n
1071  } else if (oc == 'N' || oc == 'n') {
1072  osig.modify(i, nc);
1073  last_ok = i + 1;
1074  } else {
1075  err_buf.reset();
1076  err_buf << fmt::format("Old spec at position {} should be n or N for ", i) << orig;
1077  signal_error(err_tok, "variant, bad orig");
1078  return;
1079  }
1080  changes << nc;
1081  }
1082  changes.kill_at(last_ok);
1083  bool need_prot = false; // Protect result and aux function
1084  for (size_t i = 0; i < last_ok; i++)
1085  if (changes[i] == 'x') need_prot = true;
1086  if (need_prot) prot = true;
1087  nsig << bf_reset << tok_base << ':' << osig;
1088  Token newfun = hash_table.locate(nsig);
1089  if (!hash_table.eqtb[newfun.eqtb_loc()].is_undefined()) {
1090  the_log << "Variant " << newfun << " already defined, not changing it.\n";
1091  return;
1092  }
1093  nsig << bf_reset << "exp_args:N" << changes;
1094  Token converter = hash_table.locate(nsig);
1095  TokenList body;
1096  body.push_back(converter);
1097  body.push_back(orig);
1098  auto *X = new Macro(body);
1099  mac_define(newfun, X, true, rd_always, prot ? userp_cmd : user_cmd);
1100  if (!hash_table.eqtb[converter.eqtb_loc()].is_undefined()) return;
1101  TokenList cb;
1102  for (size_t i = 0;; i++) {
1103  char c = changes[i];
1104  if (c == 0) c = ':';
1105  nsig << bf_reset << "::" << c;
1106  cb.push_back(hash_table.locate(nsig));
1107  if (c == ':') break; //
1108  }
1109  X = new Macro(cb);
1110  mac_define(converter, X, true, rd_always, need_prot ? userp_cmd : user_cmd);
1111 }

1113 // Implements: \def\::n #1\::: #2#3{#1\:::{#2{#3}}}
1114 // #2 is function to call, #3 arg to handle, #1 more things to do
1115 // NOTE: Case of last_unbraced variant. here #1 should be empty
1116 // Expansion is #2{#3} in case #1 is empty.
1117 void Parser::E_l3expand_aux(subtypes c) {
1118  Token T = cur_tok;
1119  TokenList L1, L2, L3, res;
1120  if (tracing_macros()) the_log << lg_start << T << " is expanded " << lg_end;
1121  L1 = read_until(T3col_tok);
1122  L2 = read_arg();
1123  switch (c) { // read and start handling the argument
1124  case l3expc_code:
1125  case l3expv_code:
1126  case l3expvu_code: csname_arg(); break;
1127  case l3expo_code:
1128  case l3expou_code: l3_expand_o(L3); break;
1129  case l3expf_code:
1130  case l3expfu_code: l3_expand_f(L3); break;
1131  case l3expx_code:
1132  case l3expxu_code: l3_expand_x(L3); break;
1133  case l3expp_code: // this is special
1134  L3 = read_until(hash_table.OB_token);
1135  back_input(hash_table.OB_token);
1136  break;
1137  default: L3 = read_arg();
1138  }
1139  // Interprets third argment
1140  switch (c) {
1141  case l3expn_code: // \::n normal case
1142  case l3expo_code: // \::o argument is processed
1143  case l3expf_code: // \::f ditto
1144  case l3expx_code: // \::x ditto
1145  brace_me(L3);
1146  break;
1147  case l3expc_code: // \::c is \csname#3\csname
1148  get_token();
1149  L3.push_back(cur_tok);
1150  break;
1151  case l3expV_code: // \::V case of a list
1152  case l3expv_code: // \::v case of a csname unread
1153  l3_expand_Vv(L3, c == l3expv_code);
1154  brace_me(L3);
1155  break;
1156  case l3expVu_code: // \::v_unbraced idem, unbraced
1157  case l3expvu_code: l3_expand_Vv(L3, c == l3expvu_code); break;
1158  default: // \::N \::p there is nothing to do; idem for other unbraced variants
1159  break;
1160  }
1161  // returns #1 \::: {#2#3} with #3 interpreted
1162  // if #1 is empty, this simplifies to #2#3
1163  L2.splice(L2.end(), L3);
1164  if (!L1.empty()) {
1165  res.splice(res.end(), L1);
1166  res.push_back(T3col_tok);
1167  brace_me(L2);
1168  }
1169  res.splice(res.end(), L2);
1170  if (tracing_macros()) the_log << lg_start << T << lg_arrow << res << lg_end;
1171  back_input(res);
1172 }

1174 // Case of \exp_not:c and variant. Expands according to the variant,
1175 // and prevents further expansion (via \unexpanded in general).
1176 
1177 void Parser::E_l3noexpand(subtypes c) {
1178  Token T = cur_tok;
1179  bool b = tracing_macros();
1180  TokenList L3, res;
1181  if (b) the_log << lg_start << T << " is expanded " << lg_end;
1182  switch (c) {
1183  case l3expc_code:
1184  csname_arg(); // optimise, there is a single token
1185  back_input(T_exp_notN);
1186  if (b) the_log << lg_start << T << "->\\noexpand " << cur_tok << lg_end;
1187  return;
1188  case l3expv_code:
1189  csname_arg();
1190  l3_expand_Vv(L3, true);
1191  break;
1192  case l3expV_code:
1193  L3 = read_arg();
1194  l3_expand_Vv(L3, false);
1195  break;
1196  case l3expo_code: l3_expand_o(L3); break;
1197  case l3expf_code:
1198  l3_expand_f(L3);
1199  break;
1200  break;
1201  // case l3expN_code: this is \noexpand
1202  // case l3expp_code: no need to noexpand something like #1#2
1203  // case l3expn_code: this is \unexpanded
1204  // case l3expx_code: not needed, everything is expanded
1205  default: return; // should not happen
1206  }
1207  brace_me(L3);
1208  res.push_back(T_exp_notn);
1209  res.splice(res.end(), L3);
1210  if (b) the_log << lg_start << T << lg_arrow << res << lg_end;
1211  back_input(res);
1212 }
